column3: Write a function that performs simple linear regression using the least squares method. The function should take two vectors x and y as input and return the slope and intercept of the regression line.

Write a function that performs ridge regression. The function should take a design matrix \( X \), a target vector \( y \), and a regularization parameter \( \lambda \) as input, and return the coefficient vector \( \beta \). Assume that \( X \) does not include a column of ones for the intercept.
